1125
00:09:47,980 --> 00:09:50,570
The king of Goa, huh?

1126
00:09:50,950 --> 00:09:55,410
It's a peaceful rural kingdom,
but it's home to quite a few outlaws.

1127
00:09:55,410 --> 00:10:00,080
Garp's an exception, but there's Dragon,
the Commander-in-Chief of the Revolutionary Army,

1128
00:10:00,080 --> 00:10:04,710
his Chief of Staff Sabo,
and the pirates Fire Fist and Straw Hat.

1129
00:10:04,710 --> 00:10:07,210
What an intriguing place!

1130
00:10:07,210 --> 00:10:11,920
Now, prostrate yourself before me, Garp!

1131
00:10:11,920 --> 00:10:13,260
Move it!

1132
00:10:13,260 --> 00:10:14,840
Your face irritates me!

1133
00:10:16,300 --> 00:10:19,220
His insolence leaves me speechless!

1134
00:10:22,180 --> 00:10:24,480
I'll cut to the chase, Garp.

1135
00:10:24,480 --> 00:10:25,690
Huh?

1136
00:10:25,690 --> 00:10:28,190
How do I form a connection
with the world nobles?

1137
00:10:28,190 --> 00:10:31,240
My wish is to become a Celestial Dragon.

1138
00:10:31,240 --> 00:10:33,280
So you wanna be a scumbag?

1139
00:10:35,700 --> 00:10:37,450
What?!

1140
00:10:37,450 --> 00:10:41,830
Is he serious?! We could
be put to death for that!

1141
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:44,460
Right! I can't say that.

1142
00:10:44,460 --> 00:10:45,710
Forget I said anything.

1143
00:10:47,290 --> 00:10:48,920
This guy is scary!

1144
00:10:54,970 --> 00:10:57,850
Are you okay-jamon, young man?

1145
00:10:57,850 --> 00:10:58,720
What?

1146
00:10:58,720 --> 00:11:00,140
He moved?!

1147
00:11:00,140 --> 00:11:02,560
I thought he was a building!

1148
00:11:02,560 --> 00:11:04,350
Then is he a giant?

1149
00:11:04,350 --> 00:11:08,060
I heard they eat humans
and dissolve rocks with their saliva.

1150
00:11:10,440 --> 00:11:11,650
No, wait...

1151
00:11:11,650 --> 00:11:13,280
What are these guys?!

1152
00:11:13,280 --> 00:11:14,450
Sharp teeth?

1153
00:11:14,450 --> 00:11:15,650
Scales?!

1154
00:11:16,070 --> 00:11:18,620
And what's with their skin colors?

1155
00:11:18,620 --> 00:11:21,950
Are they those half-fish, the fishmen?!

1156
00:11:21,950 --> 00:11:26,710
They're classified as fish, and people catch
rare diseases just by touching them.

1157
00:11:26,710 --> 00:11:29,420
Don't touch me!

1158
00:11:35,550 --> 00:11:38,140
Bondola 2, now departing.

1159
00:11:44,310 --> 00:11:46,390
All right, take care of yourself!

1160
00:11:46,890 --> 00:11:51,020
Sir Luffy's dear grandfather...
Thank you very much!

1161
00:11:51,020 --> 00:11:53,110
It was fun to travel with you!

1162
00:12:11,590 --> 00:12:12,920
It's so high.

1163
00:12:13,710 --> 00:12:15,340
Unbelievable!

1164
00:12:19,840 --> 00:12:22,220
What's the matter-jamon, Shirahoshi?

1165
00:12:28,890 --> 00:12:30,270
Father...

1166
00:12:31,060 --> 00:12:32,900
It's the sun.

1167
00:12:32,900 --> 00:12:37,030
Brother! The sun is shining so brightly!

1168
00:12:37,030 --> 00:12:38,240
Yeah!

1169
00:12:39,150 --> 00:12:42,620
The sky goes on forever!

1170
00:12:42,620 --> 00:12:48,040
Also, the sea is endless
and sparkles in the sun!

1171
00:12:48,040 --> 00:12:51,710
Yeah, it's really amazing!

1172
00:12:51,710 --> 00:12:53,040
♪ Mambo! ♪

1173
00:12:55,300 --> 00:12:59,050
I never knew the surface
would be so dazzling!

1174
00:12:59,380 --> 00:13:01,800
What a beautiful world!

1175
00:13:03,640 --> 00:13:08,520
The Sunlight Tree that lights up
the sea floor can't compare-jamon.

1176
00:13:13,770 --> 00:13:17,230
Father, I...

1177
00:13:17,230 --> 00:13:21,070
If possible, I want to live up on the surface!

1178
00:13:21,740 --> 00:13:27,950
I would like to share this world
of sunlight with our people.

1179
00:13:30,660 --> 00:13:34,710
Then let us ask. That's why we
came to the Reverie-jamon.

1180
00:13:34,710 --> 00:13:37,380
The Holy Land
Mary Geoise

1181
00:13:42,890 --> 00:13:47,720
Sakazuki said to find and send you
packing from this place.

1182
00:13:51,020 --> 00:13:52,350
Is that a challenge?

1183
00:13:54,610 --> 00:13:56,230
No thanks!

1184
00:13:56,230 --> 00:13:57,900
That'd be a pain in the ass!

1185
00:13:57,900 --> 00:14:01,280
And even you wouldn't think
to destroy this place, right?

1186
00:14:02,610 --> 00:14:04,910
Not especially...

1187
00:14:04,910 --> 00:14:07,160
If I'm to destroy anything...

1188
00:14:08,490 --> 00:14:10,200
it's the system itself.

1189
00:14:11,870 --> 00:14:14,000
Thank you for the meal.

1190
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:15,580
It was delicious!

1191
00:14:15,580 --> 00:14:17,290
You've traveled a ways to get here.

1192
00:14:17,290 --> 00:14:20,510
How's that old geezer Vegapunk?

1193
00:14:20,510 --> 00:14:26,390
Though I could not behold it,
he has completed something incredible.

1194
00:14:26,390 --> 00:14:27,600
Oh?

1195
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:28,810
And that would be...?

1196
00:14:31,310 --> 00:14:35,810
We no longer need
the Seven Warlords of the Sea!

1197
00:14:37,360 --> 00:14:40,530
You're crazy! Seriously!

1198
00:14:41,690 --> 00:14:45,740
Anyway, the food here
is as good as I expected!

1199
00:14:45,740 --> 00:14:47,990
You should try a bite.

1200
00:14:47,990 --> 00:14:51,750
Or are you still fasting?

1201
00:14:49,330 --> 00:14:55,580
Admiral Ryokugyu
Marine Headquarters

1202
00:14:53,120 --> 00:14:58,000
I might just eat if it were a young lady feeding me.

1203
00:14:58,000 --> 00:15:02,380
I guess I can't be bothered! I haven't
eaten a thing for three years now!

1204
00:15:04,010 --> 00:15:08,510
The Red Line

1205
00:15:08,890 --> 00:15:11,140
We're so high! Scary!

1206
00:15:11,140 --> 00:15:14,690
The wind is making us shake!

1207
00:15:22,860 --> 00:15:24,610
You're far too noisy.

1208
00:15:24,610 --> 00:15:27,530
D-D-Did you just see that?!

1209
00:15:27,530 --> 00:15:29,530
Pray tell, what did you see?

1210
00:15:29,530 --> 00:15:33,660
Just now, a g-giant was
staring at us from within the wall!

1211
00:15:33,660 --> 00:15:36,330
H-H-He had a trident!

1212
00:15:36,830 --> 00:15:38,750
Clearly, you're hallucinating...

1213
00:15:38,750 --> 00:15:40,920
Consider our tremendous altitude.

1214
00:15:40,920 --> 00:15:43,260
But I really saw it!

1215
00:15:45,590 --> 00:15:48,010
And look there! Now there are crows!

1216
00:15:48,010 --> 00:15:49,930
It's strange to see them so high.

1217
00:15:53,720 --> 00:15:56,560
Are these the birds I've heard about in stories?

1218
00:15:56,560 --> 00:15:58,230
Look how they fly!

1219
00:15:58,230 --> 00:16:02,230
If they peck at the bubble, we'll fall!

1220
00:16:02,610 --> 00:16:03,900
Hey, guard!

1221
00:16:03,900 --> 00:16:05,030
Pull out your gun!

1222
00:16:05,030 --> 00:16:07,070
Shoot down the crows!

1223
00:16:07,070 --> 00:16:08,990
They'll pop the bubble!

1224
00:16:10,950 --> 00:16:12,280
Don't worry.

1225
00:16:12,280 --> 00:16:14,290
Please rest assured...

1226
00:16:14,290 --> 00:16:16,210
King Sterry.

1227
00:16:17,330 --> 00:16:21,590
Eventually, the bondola arrives
at the top of the Red Line.

1228
00:16:24,300 --> 00:16:26,300
Thank you for riding with us.

1229
00:16:26,300 --> 00:16:28,300
Please watch your step.

1230
00:16:31,260 --> 00:16:32,720
Merfolk!

1231
00:16:33,310 --> 00:16:37,730
Your bubbles can't handle this new climate,
so use these reinforced ones.

1232
00:16:38,980 --> 00:16:39,900
Thank you!

1233
00:16:42,860 --> 00:16:44,690
Wow, it's enormous!

1234
00:16:45,150 --> 00:16:52,950
Guests must climb this large staircase to reach
the top of the world's largest continent,

1235
00:16:52,950 --> 00:16:55,990
at the very center of the world.

1236
00:16:59,080 --> 00:17:01,580
I need someone to carry me on their back!

1237
00:17:01,580 --> 00:17:04,040
We're almost there, King Sterry.

1238
00:17:15,390 --> 00:17:20,190
Those descended from the world's
creators reside here.

1239
00:17:20,640 --> 00:17:23,360
The name of this magnificent place is...

1240
00:17:24,650 --> 00:17:26,940
the Holy Land, Mary Geoise.

1241
00:17:29,320 --> 00:17:32,200
This is where the Celestial Dragons live.

1242
00:17:32,200 --> 00:17:34,660
I wanna live here!

1243
00:17:34,660 --> 00:17:36,660
What a beautiful place!

1244
00:17:36,660 --> 00:17:39,290
Is that green area a forest?

1245
00:17:39,290 --> 00:17:41,000
Yes, a man-made one.

1246
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:43,540
So this is Mary Geoise!

1247
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:49,920
The castle's still a ways off...

1248
00:17:50,340 --> 00:17:52,130
Everyone, please come this way.

1249
00:17:55,970 --> 00:17:59,390
Her Highness Shirahoshi's party
will kindly use these handles!

1250
00:18:06,480 --> 00:18:07,610
Is it an earthquake?!

1251
00:18:07,610 --> 00:18:09,990
It's started moving!

1252
00:18:09,990 --> 00:18:12,570
I'm gonna die! Save me!

1253
00:18:13,820 --> 00:18:15,320
This is a travelator.

1254
00:18:15,320 --> 00:18:16,910
It moves the very ground.

1255
00:18:18,910 --> 00:18:22,370
Father, shall we take the regular walkway?

1256
00:18:22,370 --> 00:18:25,080
Shirahoshi, you wanted
to see the forest, right?

1257
00:18:25,540 --> 00:18:26,670
Fukaboshi...

1258
00:18:27,960 --> 00:18:29,710
The scenery is beautiful!

1259
00:18:29,710 --> 00:18:31,170
Let's take our time!

1260
00:18:31,170 --> 00:18:33,760
Oh, that's a lovely idea, Brother!

1261
00:18:33,760 --> 00:18:36,510
Well, Father? Shall we?

1262
00:18:36,510 --> 00:18:38,510
I don't see why not!

1263
00:18:38,510 --> 00:18:40,140
– Allow us to escort you!
– Allow us to escort you!

1264
00:18:41,140 --> 00:18:44,190
I bet they're afraid of modern technology!

1265
00:18:44,190 --> 00:18:46,060
Stupid fish!

1266
00:18:46,480 --> 00:18:49,480
Let's procure one for Goa!

1267
00:18:49,480 --> 00:18:51,900
This troublowter is so useful!

1268
00:18:51,900 --> 00:18:52,990
It's a "travelator."

1269
00:18:52,990 --> 00:18:54,950
You can call it that too!

1270
00:18:56,200 --> 00:18:57,410
What's this?

1271
00:18:58,120 --> 00:18:59,990
Something feels wrong...

1272
00:19:00,490 --> 00:19:04,410
Underground

1273
00:19:05,540 --> 00:19:08,670
Move at a nice, slow and steady speed!

1274
00:19:08,670 --> 00:19:10,880
Keep one pace with the other slaves!

1275
00:19:12,760 --> 00:19:15,800
Don't stop! Keep it moving!

1276
00:19:18,050 --> 00:19:19,640
Save me...

1277
00:19:19,640 --> 00:19:21,770
or just kill me!

1278
00:19:23,350 --> 00:19:26,230
A Certain Celestial Dragon's Mansion

1279
00:19:26,230 --> 00:19:29,440
Daddy dearest! Daddy dearest!

1280
00:19:29,440 --> 00:19:31,440
What is it, Charlos?

1281
00:19:32,280 --> 00:19:33,940
It's a mermaid!

1282
00:19:34,440 --> 00:19:36,410
A very big one!

1283
00:19:47,040 --> 00:19:48,460
Open the gate!

1284
00:19:58,010 --> 00:20:01,140
A Courtyard Within the Castle

1285
00:20:02,470 --> 00:20:06,810
Seems like royal families and their bodyguards
from across the world are here.

1286
00:20:07,730 --> 00:20:10,020
Their bodyguards look formidable.

1287
00:20:10,020 --> 00:20:11,770
We're probably safe here.

1288
00:20:12,900 --> 00:20:15,860
The food looks fancy too!

1289
00:20:15,860 --> 00:20:21,370
If every day of the seven-day
conference is so festive,

1290
00:20:21,370 --> 00:20:27,250
none of the families attending
will get bored-fa-mi-re-do! ♪

1291
00:20:27,250 --> 00:20:31,960
We love samba more than anything!
Would you like to dance with us?!

1292
00:20:31,960 --> 00:20:32,960
♪ Samba! ♪

1293
00:20:32,960 --> 00:20:35,380
I'd be happy to, King of Samba!

1294
00:20:35,380 --> 00:20:36,340
♪ Mambo! ♪

1295
00:20:36,340 --> 00:20:39,590
– ♪ Mambo, mambo! Shake, shake! ♪
– ♪ Samba, samba! Shake, shake! ♪

1296
00:20:39,590 --> 00:20:42,010
Even Father is enjoying himself.

1297
00:20:42,010 --> 00:20:43,560
That's a relief.

1298
00:20:45,270 --> 00:20:47,350
U-Um...

1299
00:20:48,480 --> 00:20:50,270
L-Lords and l-ladies...?

1300
00:20:50,270 --> 00:20:53,060
O, dear Princess from under the sea!

1301
00:20:53,060 --> 00:20:56,150
The rumors do your beauty justice!

1302
00:20:56,150 --> 00:20:57,990
I'd like you to meet my son.

1303
00:20:57,990 --> 00:20:59,990
He's royalty and single!

1304
00:20:59,990 --> 00:21:03,070
Papan! Not bad. Not bad at all!

1305
00:21:03,070 --> 00:21:04,620
U-Um...

1306
00:21:04,620 --> 00:21:08,870
Your Royal Highness, our son—
also a royal—is available!

1307
00:21:08,870 --> 00:21:11,500
P-Pappy! I like her!

1308
00:21:11,500 --> 00:21:13,040
Um... uh...

1309
00:21:13,040 --> 00:21:14,540
No, Mermaid Princess!

1310
00:21:14,540 --> 00:21:16,920
Please meet my royal son!

1311
00:21:18,260 --> 00:21:22,010
Our royal family has three handsome sons!

1312
00:21:23,430 --> 00:21:26,520
– Now, which royal suitor do you like?!
– Now, which royal suitor do you like?!

1313
00:21:26,520 --> 00:21:29,140
Oh, um... uh...

1314
00:21:32,560 --> 00:21:35,480
Um... well...

1315
00:21:36,110 --> 00:21:37,730
None of you are my type!

1316
00:21:37,730 --> 00:21:41,400
– What?! Even though they're royalty?!
– What?! Even though they're royalty?!

1317
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:43,450
– Shirahoshi!
– Shirahoshi!

1318
00:21:44,370 --> 00:21:45,490
How dare you!

1319
00:21:45,490 --> 00:21:47,450
This is humiliating!

1320
00:21:48,790 --> 00:21:52,120
No, my sister was saying
"I'm not married, either."

1321
00:21:52,120 --> 00:21:55,130
That is, in an undersea dialect...

1322
00:21:55,130 --> 00:21:57,250
Ryuboshi...?!

1323
00:21:57,250 --> 00:22:01,510
When this happens, just say "How lovely"
or "Let's have dinner sometime,"

1324
00:22:01,510 --> 00:22:04,010
and turn them down gracefully, Shirahoshi!

1325
00:22:05,260 --> 00:22:07,350
But I'm not a liar...

1326
00:22:07,350 --> 00:22:09,810
It's just dodging, not lying!

1327
00:22:09,810 --> 00:22:13,440
If you upset someone, it could become
a international issue-fa-mi-re-do! ♪

1328
00:22:13,440 --> 00:22:14,940
Let's go!

1329
00:22:18,020 --> 00:22:19,690
How cute!

1330
00:22:20,240 --> 00:22:24,320
Princess Vivi and Karoo
Kingdom of Alabasta

1331
00:22:21,070 --> 00:22:22,700
You're so cute!

1332
00:22:22,700 --> 00:22:24,320
You're like a fairy!

1333
00:22:24,320 --> 00:22:27,990
That's not a compliment to a warrior!

1334
00:22:24,490 --> 00:22:27,990
Commander Leo
Tonta Corps, Tontatta Tribe

1335
00:22:28,370 --> 00:22:31,370
Mansherry

1336
00:22:28,370 --> 00:22:31,370
Kabu

1337
00:22:28,370 --> 00:22:31,370
Bian

1338
00:22:29,330 --> 00:22:31,370
Are you okay, Leo?!

1339
00:22:31,370 --> 00:22:33,290
Oh, I'm sorry!

1340
00:22:33,290 --> 00:22:34,790
I didn't mean to offend!

1341
00:22:34,790 --> 00:22:35,420
What?!

1342
00:22:36,170 --> 00:22:37,750
In that case, it's fine!

1343
00:22:38,090 --> 00:22:39,170
Oh, good!

1344
00:22:39,170 --> 00:22:40,590
She seems nice!

1345
00:22:40,590 --> 00:22:45,550
You're really quick. I wouldn't have
noticed you if it weren't for Karoo.

1346
00:22:45,890 --> 00:22:50,430
I showed myself because I heard
you say you knew Luffyland.

1347
00:22:50,430 --> 00:22:53,140
We're subordinates of Luffyland's crew!

1348
00:22:53,140 --> 00:22:54,770
We're pirates!

1349
00:22:54,770 --> 00:22:56,940
Pirates?!

1350
00:22:56,940 --> 00:22:58,650
So cute!

1351
00:22:58,650 --> 00:23:00,400
It's nice to meet you, Leo!

1352
00:23:00,400 --> 00:23:02,690
Nice to meet you, too!

1353
00:23:02,690 --> 00:23:07,280
I never thought I'd be able to talk
so much about Lucy at the Reverie.

1354
00:23:08,660 --> 00:23:12,830
But it only makes sense if
they're traveling the world.

1355
00:23:08,990 --> 00:23:14,710
Rebecca
A Dressrosan Lady-in-Waiting

1356
00:23:12,830 --> 00:23:14,710
Did Lucy visit your country, Vivi?

1357
00:23:15,670 --> 00:23:17,040
Rather, did Luffy?

1358
00:23:17,040 --> 00:23:19,380
That's right! Luffyland!

1359
00:23:20,090 --> 00:23:21,000
Yes.

1360
00:23:21,500 --> 00:23:24,970
My home country, Alabasta,
only exists today...

1361
00:23:24,970 --> 00:23:27,050
thanks to them.

1362
00:23:27,590 --> 00:23:33,180
Princess Vivi hails from Alabasta,
the Kingdom of Sand in the Grand Line,

1363
00:23:33,180 --> 00:23:39,110
and years ago became friends with the Straw Hats,
even sailing with them for some time.

1364
00:23:39,980 --> 00:23:42,650
In order to take control of the country,

1365
00:23:42,650 --> 00:23:45,650
the former Warlord Sir Crocodile

1366
00:23:45,650 --> 00:23:49,820
instigated a civil war between
the Royal Army and the Rebellion.

1367
00:23:50,280 --> 00:23:56,120
Luffy and his crew foiled Crocodile's plot
and saved the Kingdom of Alabasta.

1368
00:23:56,120 --> 00:23:59,960
However, the Straw Hats didn't get the credit,

1369
00:23:59,960 --> 00:24:03,920
because the government reported it
as a Marine accomplishment.

1370
00:24:04,510 --> 00:24:07,220
Since they never want to be seen as heroes...

1371
00:24:07,760 --> 00:24:12,640
they received bounties and earned
infamy instead of fame, but...

1372
00:24:12,640 --> 00:24:16,100
I'm sure they haven't changed.

1373
00:24:16,100 --> 00:24:19,310
When I read about Dressrosa...

1374
00:24:19,310 --> 00:24:24,690
I knew that Luffy and his crew
had decided to save somebody again!

1375
00:24:25,400 --> 00:24:29,030
– That's right!
– That's right!

1376
00:24:27,820 --> 00:24:29,030
Huh?

1377
00:24:29,030 --> 00:24:31,160
To us, Luffy...

1378
00:24:31,160 --> 00:24:35,450
The Straw Hats mean the world to us.

1379
00:24:40,250 --> 00:24:42,590
I miss Lucy.

1380
00:24:44,590 --> 00:24:45,840
Um...

1381
00:24:46,720 --> 00:24:51,140
Were you talking about Sir Luffy just now?

1382
00:24:50,590 --> 00:24:51,140
Huh?

1383
00:24:51,140 --> 00:24:52,720
Oh, the Mermaid Princess!

1384
00:24:54,060 --> 00:24:55,350
Shirahoshi!

1385
00:24:56,060 --> 00:24:58,810
Talking about him doesn't
mean they know him!

1386
00:24:58,810 --> 00:25:00,560
Luffy is a pirate!

1387
00:25:00,560 --> 00:25:03,440
No one can know he's your friend-la-ti-do! ♪

1388
00:25:05,030 --> 00:25:07,360
The Mermaid Princess knows Luffy?

1389
00:25:07,360 --> 00:25:09,990
Hey, did you say "Sir Luffy" just now?

1390
00:25:09,990 --> 00:25:11,360
Wait, Rebecca!

1391
00:25:11,360 --> 00:25:13,030
If we heard wrong...

1392
00:25:13,030 --> 00:25:13,700
Yes!

1393
00:25:13,700 --> 00:25:14,950
I did!

1394
00:25:14,950 --> 00:25:16,580
Do you know him?!

1395
00:25:16,580 --> 00:25:17,450
Stop!

1396
00:25:17,450 --> 00:25:19,370
Everyone knows his name!

1397
00:25:19,370 --> 00:25:23,130
I'm deeply indebted to Sir Luffy.

1398
00:25:26,170 --> 00:25:27,260
– So are we!
– So are we!

1399
00:25:49,240 --> 00:25:53,110
Hey, Luffy sure eats a lot, doesn't he?

1400
00:25:53,110 --> 00:25:56,910
Uh-huh! He had an unbelievable
appetite on Dressrosa!

1401
00:25:57,790 --> 00:26:00,290
It was the same at Ryugu Palace.

1402
00:26:00,290 --> 00:26:02,170
They're having fun.

1403
00:26:02,170 --> 00:26:03,290
They really are.

1404
00:26:03,290 --> 00:26:09,050
It's a good sign when those responsible
for the future of their countries get along.

1405
00:26:09,050 --> 00:26:11,930
Even though it's a peculiar connection.

1406
00:26:11,930 --> 00:26:16,390
Yes, it's all thanks 
to Straw Hat and his crew.

1407
00:26:17,430 --> 00:26:21,390
Hey! Aren't you Rebecca from Dressrosa?!

1408
00:26:22,560 --> 00:26:24,150
Oh, I know him!

1409
00:26:25,190 --> 00:26:26,650
It's me, Sai!

1410
00:26:25,400 --> 00:26:30,400
Sai
13th Don of the Happo Navy

1411
00:26:26,650 --> 00:26:30,400
I didn't expect to see you again so soon!

1412
00:26:30,400 --> 00:26:32,030
How have you been?!

1413
00:26:32,030 --> 00:26:33,530
I'm doing fine!

1414
00:26:33,910 --> 00:26:37,030
He's from Kano's Happo Navy.

1415
00:26:37,030 --> 00:26:41,410
I heard he replaced Chinjao as leader.

1416
00:26:41,410 --> 00:26:43,790
Yes, he's the new don.

1417
00:26:44,170 --> 00:26:45,250
Sai!

1418
00:26:46,130 --> 00:26:47,710
Hey there, Brother!

1419
00:26:47,710 --> 00:26:50,170
You came too, Leo!

1420
00:26:50,170 --> 00:26:51,800
I'm a secret bodyguard!

1421
00:26:53,130 --> 00:26:54,930
You're so reliable!

1422
00:26:54,930 --> 00:26:55,590
Right?

1423
00:26:56,470 --> 00:26:58,390
Is he a friend?

1424
00:26:58,390 --> 00:27:02,310
We both swore an oath to Luffyland.

1425
00:27:02,730 --> 00:27:03,690
Leo.

1426
00:27:03,690 --> 00:27:07,400
Up until now, I've been working for Kano,

1427
00:27:07,400 --> 00:27:10,780
but I'm cutting ties once I
finish up here as a bodyguard.

1428
00:27:10,780 --> 00:27:14,400
This will be my last service for them.

1429
00:27:14,400 --> 00:27:19,700
I'm deeply indebted to Straw Hat
and the others for saving us in Dressrosa.

1430
00:27:20,160 --> 00:27:25,710
The Straw Hat Grand Fleet
numbers over 5,600 total troops.

1431
00:27:25,710 --> 00:27:29,840
We seven representatives should
be ready to assist him at a moment's notice.

1432
00:27:31,800 --> 00:27:35,630
The others are preparing too.

1433
00:27:42,640 --> 00:27:43,850
What did you say?!

1434
00:27:43,310 --> 00:27:43,350
Resignation

1435
00:27:43,350 --> 00:27:43,470
Resignation

1436
00:27:43,470 --> 00:27:43,600
Resignation

1437
00:27:43,600 --> 00:27:43,730
Resignation

1438
00:27:43,730 --> 00:27:43,850
Resignation

1439
00:27:43,850 --> 00:27:48,230
You're suddenly leaving
the Standing Kingdom?!

1440
00:27:43,850 --> 00:27:43,980
Resignation

1441
00:27:43,980 --> 00:27:44,100
Resignation

1442
00:27:44,730 --> 00:27:44,850
Resignation

1443
00:27:44,850 --> 00:27:44,980
Resignation

1444
00:27:44,980 --> 00:27:45,100
Resignation

1445
00:27:45,100 --> 00:27:45,190
Resignation

1446
00:27:48,230 --> 00:27:49,480
Explain yourself!

1447
00:27:49,900 --> 00:27:52,780
I owe someone a great debt.

1448
00:27:52,780 --> 00:27:54,360
Barrier!

1449
00:27:54,740 --> 00:27:56,990
Barrier Crash!

1450
00:27:58,740 --> 00:28:02,120
You put up a barrier by crossing your fingers.

1451
00:28:02,120 --> 00:28:04,750
Even children know that!

1452
00:28:05,250 --> 00:28:06,870
W-We surrender!

1453
00:28:06,870 --> 00:28:08,580
We lose!

1454
00:28:08,580 --> 00:28:11,420
We'll serve under you, so spare us!

1455
00:28:12,630 --> 00:28:14,010
Well then...

1456
00:28:14,010 --> 00:28:15,300
Put this on.

1457
00:28:16,670 --> 00:28:18,050
Wh-What is it?

1458
00:28:19,840 --> 00:28:23,510
Let's all support the Straw Hats!

1459
00:28:23,510 --> 00:28:24,720
– Let's!
– Let's!

1460
00:28:28,810 --> 00:28:31,900
Two unidentified ships are approaching!

1461
00:28:31,900 --> 00:28:34,400
Are they remnants of Doflamingo's forces?

1462
00:28:35,530 --> 00:28:36,820
Cavendish.

1463
00:28:36,820 --> 00:28:39,070
As you may know...

1464
00:28:39,820 --> 00:28:43,580
I'm the former prince of Bourgeois.

1465
00:28:45,290 --> 00:28:48,750
– Prince Cavendish!
– Prince Cavendish!

1466
00:28:48,750 --> 00:28:53,500
But all the women in the country
were crazy about me...

1467
00:28:54,130 --> 00:28:56,970
and not a single one was willing
to marry another man.

1468
00:28:57,380 --> 00:29:02,390
I was expelled from the country
for being too popular.

1469
00:29:03,100 --> 00:29:04,600
So...

1470
00:29:05,010 --> 00:29:08,980
we don't need to attack them
since they're not our enemies.

1471
00:29:12,810 --> 00:29:20,240
Straw Hat is now sure to face far more
dangerous opponents than Doflamingo.

1472
00:29:20,240 --> 00:29:23,280
We have to become stronger.

1473
00:29:23,280 --> 00:29:24,450
Yes!

1474
00:29:24,450 --> 00:29:27,200
My crew and I are training too!

1475
00:29:27,200 --> 00:29:31,210
I hope we can fight together
for Luffyland again!

1476
00:29:31,210 --> 00:29:32,540
Yeah!

1477
00:29:37,960 --> 00:29:40,470
Well, well, Princess Vivi!

1478
00:29:41,630 --> 00:29:42,680
Wapol!

1479
00:29:43,220 --> 00:29:46,850
King Wapol
Evil Kingdom of Black Drum

1480
00:29:45,050 --> 00:29:46,310
You hippo!

1481
00:29:47,140 --> 00:29:49,520
Queen Kinderella
Evil Kingdom of Black Drum

1482
00:29:49,520 --> 00:29:51,480
What are you doing here?!

1483
00:29:53,520 --> 00:29:55,020
It must seem strange, right?

1484
00:29:55,020 --> 00:30:02,910
Sure, Straw Hat Luffy sent me
flying to a distant sea!

1485
00:30:02,910 --> 00:30:04,370
But now I'm back!

1486
00:30:04,370 --> 00:30:07,910
Do you wanna know
how my darling came back?

1487
00:30:08,290 --> 00:30:11,750
Is he Sir Luffy's friend, too?

1488
00:30:11,750 --> 00:30:13,000
No.

1489
00:30:13,000 --> 00:30:14,460
He's an enemy, Shirahoshi!

1490
00:30:16,340 --> 00:30:19,380
Old "Straight-laced"
King Cobra is well, I hope?

1491
00:30:19,380 --> 00:30:20,630
Oh, pardon me.

1492
00:30:20,630 --> 00:30:26,140
I took note of his failing health,
so I'm just being tasteless.

1493
00:30:27,310 --> 00:30:29,220
Oh, darling!

1494
00:30:29,220 --> 00:30:32,850
You're the funniest man in the whole universe!

1495
00:30:37,270 --> 00:30:38,020
Wapol!

1496
00:30:39,820 --> 00:30:41,570
Give it a rest!

1497
00:30:42,320 --> 00:30:45,320
I can't believe you became a king again.

1498
00:30:43,990 --> 00:30:48,240
King Dalton
Sakura Kingdom

1499
00:30:45,320 --> 00:30:48,240
I pity your new country.

1500
00:30:50,160 --> 00:30:52,410
The World Government must be desperate!

1501
00:30:50,540 --> 00:30:55,790
Dr. Kureha
Sakura Kingdom

1502
00:30:52,410 --> 00:30:55,790
I can't believe they'd admit this idiot again!

1503
00:30:56,210 --> 00:30:58,500
Dalton! The old witch hag!

1504
00:30:58,500 --> 00:31:00,380
You're still alive?!

1505
00:31:00,380 --> 00:31:02,470
Huh? Wanna know the secret to my youth?

1506
00:31:02,470 --> 00:31:03,760
I wasn't asking!

1507
00:31:03,760 --> 00:31:06,050
Dalton! Dr. Kureha!

1508
00:31:06,050 --> 00:31:07,640
It's nice to see you again!

1509
00:31:07,640 --> 00:31:09,390
It's a pleasure, Vivi.

1510
00:31:09,390 --> 00:31:11,520
You look more dignified than ever.

1511
00:31:12,890 --> 00:31:14,270
Are ya happy?

1512
00:31:14,270 --> 00:31:20,230
If I had known you were a princess back then,
your medical bills would've been much higher.

1513
00:31:20,820 --> 00:31:22,610
Who are these people?

1514
00:31:22,610 --> 00:31:26,360
I met them while I was traveling
with Luffy and his crew.

1515
00:31:30,080 --> 00:31:36,000
Nami became ill on our way to Alabasta,
so to find her a doctor...

1516
00:31:36,540 --> 00:31:39,710
we made landfall at a winter island.

1517
00:31:42,210 --> 00:31:46,970
Back then, Luffy helped
Dalton get rid of Wapol.

1518
00:31:47,760 --> 00:31:53,350
Following that, the citizens made him their new king
and renamed the country the Sakura Kingdom.

1519
00:31:53,350 --> 00:31:54,980
I see.

1520
00:31:56,480 --> 00:31:58,100
Hey, hey, hey!

1521
00:31:58,100 --> 00:32:04,610
Dolt-on! Where does a subordinate
get off telling me earlier to "give it a rest"?!

1522
00:32:04,610 --> 00:32:06,530
That was long ago.

1523
00:32:07,280 --> 00:32:08,160
Now...

1524
00:32:13,200 --> 00:32:16,410
we are on equal footing!

1525
00:32:17,500 --> 00:32:18,460
Darling!

1526
00:32:18,460 --> 00:32:19,880
Dalton!

1527
00:32:19,880 --> 00:32:23,000
You have mastered that kingly demeanor!

1528
00:32:23,000 --> 00:32:24,460
What? No...

1529
00:32:25,840 --> 00:32:27,220
Listen up, Dalton!

1530
00:32:27,220 --> 00:32:29,220
You bastard in shining armor!

1531
00:32:29,220 --> 00:32:33,510
An honest throne won't
help you run your country!

1532
00:32:33,510 --> 00:32:39,520
I'm living proof, since I came back by making
a fortune with my Munch-Munch Fruit power!

1533
00:32:39,520 --> 00:32:43,690
The higher you climb, the wider your view
of the corruption around you!

1534
00:32:43,690 --> 00:32:46,820
Consider this both a lesson and payback for–

1535
00:32:46,820 --> 00:32:50,450
By the way, did you read
that article about Luffy?

1536
00:32:50,450 --> 00:32:52,490
Yes, many times over.

1537
00:32:52,490 --> 00:32:55,290
Say, maybe... Dalton...

1538
00:32:56,540 --> 00:32:58,580
Do you like Lucy?

1539
00:32:58,580 --> 00:33:00,710
You like Luffyland, don't you?

1540
00:33:04,840 --> 00:33:05,880
He's the best.

1541
00:33:06,880 --> 00:33:08,630
This is gonna be fun!

1542
00:33:10,220 --> 00:33:13,930
Impel Down, the undersea prison...

1543
00:33:11,970 --> 00:33:16,220
Impel Down
The Undersea Prison

1544
00:33:21,190 --> 00:33:22,980
The lowest level.

1545
00:33:22,980 --> 00:33:25,900
It's where the most dangerous
criminals are locked away.

1546
00:33:25,900 --> 00:33:27,440
Level 6...

1547
00:33:29,030 --> 00:33:31,110
Eternal Hell.

1548
00:33:36,160 --> 00:33:39,080
What's with the solitary confinement?

1549
00:33:39,080 --> 00:33:43,040
I'm all by my lonesome here.

1550
00:33:43,040 --> 00:33:47,460
Or are you saying this is
for my protection, Magellan?!

1551
00:33:49,630 --> 00:33:51,050
Have they come for me?

1552
00:33:51,050 --> 00:33:53,430
An assassin from above?

1553
00:33:53,430 --> 00:33:59,310
They'll of course want to prevent me
from telling the secret of Mary Geoise.

1554
00:33:59,310 --> 00:34:03,770
Did they send an assassin to keep me quiet?!

1555
00:34:08,530 --> 00:34:11,280
And why should it matter if I tell?

1556
00:34:11,280 --> 00:34:16,530
Power is fleeting with corruption
close on its heels!

1557
00:34:19,200 --> 00:34:22,460
Mary Geoise
